text: Nuoro (Nùgoro) is a town and comune (municipality) in the Province of Nuoro in Sardinia, Italy. As of 2016, 36,925 people lived there. Its area is 192.06 km². It is 549 meters above sea level. == References == == Other websites == Category:Communes of the Province of Nuoro Category:Capital cities in Italy
